Review the current changes with focus on Shannon-specific patterns and common mistakes.

## Error Handling (CRITICAL)
- All errors use PentestError — never raw `Error`
- Error type is appropriate: 'config', 'network', 'tool', 'prompt', 'filesystem', 'validation', 'billing', 'unknown'
- Retryable flag matches behavior
- Context includes debugging info
- Use ErrorCode enum for classification
- Result<T,E> for service returns

## Audit System & Concurrency (CRITICAL)
- Mutex protection for parallel operations
- Reload before modify — `metricsTracker.reload()` before updating metrics
- Atomic writes for session.json — use `atomicWrite()`, never `fs.writeFile()` directly
- Stream drain handling
- Semaphore release in finally blocks

## Claude SDK Integration (CRITICAL)
- Prompt variable interpolation — check all `{{VARIABLE}}` placeholders
- Turn counting — increment on assistant messages, not tool calls
- Cost tracking — extract from final result message
- API error detection — "session limit reached" (fatal) vs other errors

## Services Layer & DI Container (CRITICAL)
- Business logic in services, not activities
- Services accept ActivityLogger — no `@temporalio/*` imports in services
- Result type for fallible operations
- AuditSession not in container — passed per-agent call

## TypeScript Safety
- No double casting (`as unknown as SomeType`)
- Validate before casting
- Explicit null checks on critical paths
- Use `??` not `||` for null/undefined defaults
- `import type { ... }` for type-only imports

## Security Review
- No credentials in logs
- Config file size limit (1MB max)
- YAML safe parsing — FAILSAFE_SCHEMA only
- No eval/Function
- Input validation at boundaries

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- Catch + re-throw without context
- Silent failures in session loading
- Duplicate retry logic
- Hardcoded error message matching
- Console.log in services — use ActivityLogger
- Temporal imports in services
